phic-events-in-history/"],"series":"","series_excerpt":"","series_part_number":"","share_twitter_text":"For Donald Trump to succeed with North Korea, he’ll need a pragmatic definition of “denuclearization”","show_donations_promo":true,"show_in_recirculation":true,"show_in_syndication":true,"show_thumbnail_caption":false,"slug":"for-donald-trump-to-succeed-with-north-korea-hell-need-a-pragmatic-definition-of-denuclearization","speakingId":"for-donald-trump-to-succeed-with-north-korea-hell-need-a-pragmatic-definition-of-denuclearization","subtype":null,"talk_cutover_date":1513620000,"talk_publish_timestamp":1524861616,"thumbnail":{"ID":185697,"alt_text":"North Korean leader Kim Jong Un, left, listens to South Korean President Moon Jae-in while walking together at the Panmunjom in the Demilitarized Zone Friday, April 27, 2018. Kim made history Friday by crossing over the world's most heavily armed border to greet his rival, Moon, for talks on North Korea's nuclear weapons. (Korea Summit Press Pool via AP)","content":"","credit":"Photo: Korea Summit Press Pool via AP","excerpt":"North Korean leader Kim Jong Un, left, listens to South Korean President Moon Jae-in while walking together at the Panmunjom in the Demilitarized Zone on April 27, 2018. ","sizes":{"article_header":{"height":720,"path":"wp-uploads/sites/1/2018/04/AP_18117194137387-featured-1524861119-article-header.jpg","width":1440},"feature_hero":{"height":800,"path":"wp-uploads/sites/1/2018/04/AP_18117194137387-featured-1524861119-feature-hero.jpg","width":1200},"original":{"height":"1500","path":"wp-uploads/sites/1/2018/04/AP_18117194137387-featured-1524861119.jpg","width":"3000"},"promo":{"height":220,"path":"wp-uploads/sites/1/2018/04/AP_18117194137387-featured-1524861119-promo.jpg","width":440},"promo_large":{"height":450,"path":"wp-uploads/sites/1/2018/04/AP_18117194137387-featured-1524861119-promo-large.jpg","width":900},"small":{"height":100,"path":"wp-uploads/sites/1/2018/04/AP_18117194137387-featured